OL,6,FThe BBC also said: "We have never said
OL,7,Fthat Gary should be an opinion free
OL,8,Fzone, or that he can't have a view on
OL,9,Fissues that matter to him, but we have
OL,10,Fsaid that he should keep well away from
OL,11,Ftaking sides on party political issues
OL,12,For political controversies."
OL,14,FHowever, on Saturday the row escalated,
OL,15,Fwith other BBC Sport presenters,
OL,16,Fpundits and commentators expressing
OL,17,Fsolidarity with Gary Lineker and
OL,18,Fwithdrawing their services for
OL,19,Fprogrammes due to air during the day on
OL,20,FBBC TV and radio.
